cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category cs.CL (Computation and Language) because it deals with natural language processing tasks such as morphological analysis and tagging. The use of neural network potentials also suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The mention of "factorial conditional random fields" indicates that it could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the mention of "surface forms" suggests that it could belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as well, since computer vision tasks often involve analyzing and processing visual surface forms.
